# Testing Requirements

## TRIGGER
When creating or modifying code that handles business logic or data processing.

## RULES

### Test Coverage
- Write unit tests for all public methods
- Test happy path and error cases
- Minimum 70% code coverage for new code

### Test Naming
- Use descriptive test names: `Should_ReturnUser_WhenIdExists`
- Follow pattern: `Method_Scenario_ExpectedResult`

### Test Structure
- Arrange: Set up test data
- Act: Execute the method being tested
- Assert: Verify the results

### Integration Tests
- Test API endpoints with realistic data
- Verify database operations work correctly
- Test error handling and edge cases

### Mocking
- Mock external dependencies (APIs, databases)
- Use dependency injection for testability
- Don't mock value objects or data structures
